README for transport
====================
Main source file: transport.cc

To compile program:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. run cmake, for example "cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=~/bin/deal.II ."
2. run make

To run program:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
$ ./transport
Output files are stored in ./output.

To edit input:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Input file: ./input

To plot the results:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Some gnuplot scripts are available in ./plotscripts:
solution.gp
viscosity.gp

For solution.gp, which plots the solution of a test problem with all
available output (corresponding to different viscosity options),
the shell script "plot" is available in the current directory. This
script must be used because gnuplot does not accept command-line arguments,
so arguments must be passed using environment variables. "plot" accomplishes
this and takes the problem ID from the input file and passes it to solution.gp.
So just run "plot" after you run the problem to plot it (and automatically view
the output).

To plot the viscosity, go into the plotscripts directory and run the viscosity.gp
script:
$ gnuplot viscosity.gp
which produces a .pdf file in the /plotscripts directory
